This specimen was collected outdoors near a greenhouse on the grounds of the Atlantic Food and Horticulture Research Centre in Kentville, Nova Scotia . This species is not found naturally in Canada and occurs no closer to the region than New York (
Dietrich 1945
). It doubtless represents an imported specimen that somehow escaped. There is no evidence that the species has established itself in Nova Scotia .
